{meta: title Two Step Around The Christmas Tree}
{meta: artist Michael Martin Murphey}
{meta: writer Suzy Bogguss and Doug Crider}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]There's a wondrous sight and a joyful sound
[G7]Every Christmas Eve in a western town
[C]Gather up the kids all the friends and family
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
Cause the holly's hung and the candle's bright
[G7]Tuning up a fiddle on a moon lit night
[C]Roll back the rug so we can two step 'round the Christmas tree
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
There's a jolly man in a bright red suit
[G7]Did you ever see a Santa in cowboy boots
[C]Twirling across the floor spurs a-jingling merrily
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
As they sing those carols soft and low
[G7]We'll all be shouting out cotton-eyed Joe
[C]Roll back the rug so we can two step 'round the Christmas tree
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
[F]Waiting 'neath the [C]mistletoe you'll [G7]never get a [C]kiss
[B]I never [C]move that slow there's [D7]too much I could [G7]miss
[C]Cause a western girl can't be still
[G7]And a silent night is not for me
[C]Roll back the rug so we can two step 'round the Christmas Tree
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
Red Bandanas chili green
[G7]Silver buckles on a new blue jeans
[C]Jumping 'round the room to a yule tide melody
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 7}
I'm gonna be ready when Santa's comes
[G7]But I'm gonna be dancing 'til he does
[C]Roll back the rug so we can two step 'round the Christmas tree
